#104   Name: Customer ()   Date: 4/21 @ 14:06 PM PST
#47's idea may work, but then again may not.

You can sue over just about anything, whether
you win or not is a different matter entirely.

I hear people (unknowledgeable ones at that) all
the time say "You can't sue them, you agreed to
their licensing agreement".

That's hogwash. You can sue, Class Action would be
the most effective. The reason being that a Court
is much more likely to look at a huge number of people
being dis-serviced as a problem than if one or 2 sued
individually.

If nothing else, even if you do not win, the spectre of
a Class action Law suit is something NO Business wants.

Can you imagine that in the Newspaper? Can you
imagine what the fallout would be for Verant if all
of the gaming websites started carrying news that
Verant was involved as the defendant in a Class Action
Lawsuit? The court of public opinion would do possibly
what a Legal court would or could not do.

GET THEIR ATTENTION!!!

Bad Planning on your part, does not mean I have
to accept your apology John Smedley. You are
the CEO of that organization and thus it's Captain.

Better put a fire under the ass of your crew before
you have a world wide mutiny on your hands.
